Reasoning: The paper deals with the characterization of the generalized degrees of freedom (GDoF) of the symmetric K-user interference channel under finite precision channel state information at the transmitters (CSIT). This falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses interference management (cs.SI) and communication complexity (cs.CC) in the context of the symmetric K-user interference channel. Additionally, the paper uses mathematical modeling and analysis (cs.MM) to derive its results.
